criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Individuals aged between 18-25 years old;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnancy;

          -  With the follow conditions: lumbar discal hernia, spondylolisthesis with neurologic
             influence, narrowing of medullar canal, rheumatic disease, orthopaedic or neurologic
             conditions such as diminished sensibility, lack or absence of muscular strength,
             absence of patellar and/or aquilus reflexes;

          -  History of chirurgical intervention either on lumbar or lower limbs in the past 6
             months;

          -  History of any trauma on the lumbar spine or lower limbs in the past 6 months;

          -  Any type of treatment on the lumbar in the previous month: that implicates
             physiotherapy, osteopathy, chiropractic, myofascial treatment, acupuncture or others;

          -  Medication that affects the vestibular system (dizziness, vertigo and humming)

          -  Pain during que experimental study;

          -  Difference between the length of the lower limbs: above 1.5cm;
